reviews.text: The owners are very helpful and nice. We got what we expected - the price was really good as well as the location. Our room even had a huge balcony overlooking the sea! We've spent a pleasant and relaxing night here. Unfortunately the owners don't speak English.
Basic hotel, good if you need to spend A night!
Old fashioned, be a tourists as they were 40 years ago. The place is beautifull un a Wes Anderson sense, but a dirty common bath kind of ruins the experience.
Old style room, dirty bathroom
Bellisimo
A magnificent building and a must- see location in Heidelberg.
Interesting to learn that the Holy Ghost might have been a girl!

Very surprised by this church, from the outside it looks like a fairly minor church in a small square, but the interior is impressive. It is painted brilliant white, with just a few gilded details, with huge frescos. The small peace garden is well designed with a few sculptures. There are two new organs in the church, which would be worth hearing if possible. A very peaceful church not far off the busy main street
Looks mesmerizing

The church is a gem that pops out in the middle of nowhere. It is located just a little bit of the main road and does not have a large yard or gardens like other churches. All-white walls on the inside are also not a typical sight in catholic churches.

One of the most beautiful palaces I have ever seen. This is not a mere exaggeration but it's the fact. The palace, the surrounding areas covered by the garden, all are very neat and clean. The museum indexed the palace gives you the glimpse of the history of the rulers of the city and their successors. Just beside it is a ground where horse races are conducted. Outside the palace entry gate is a zoo, where one can catch the glimpse of different kinds of birds in the lake beside it.

This is very interesting historic place. Very beautiful palace and a fantastic  museum. We can see  ancient  oil paintings, Rulers old photos, coins, old clothes which is used by King. There are different kinds of arms and ammunition like old guns, spears,knives,swords etc.

Another beautiful  attraction in the museum is  stuffed wild animals and birds.

* I have posted few pictures of this place. Hit 'LIKE' if they are helpful to you.

Beautiful palace with a nice collection in the museum inside the palace. An adult ticket cost Rs 35 to see the museum. Photography is strictly prohibited, you are instructed to keep your phone switched off inside the palace. The lawn is lush green, people can sit and relax and can take as many pics as they want. Ideal time to invest is 1-2 hours.

Beautiful Palace!
Nice museum of historical items, furniture,photographs, wildlife & arms etc.
Palace n surrounding area is beautiful..neat n clean! Ample space for parking.
Small garden in front of palace is well maintained.
# only inconvenience is ticket window for the museum is on main gate of palace; that should be nearby palace.

Historical place. Entrance fee is must.  Parking space. Photos are not allowed. Not crowded. Usually it takes an hour. Beautiful background to take pictures. 
Palace is maintained and lawn as well. Huge trees around. Animals are present too. Specially interesting for kids and historical lovers

(Even though it is very old it is meaningful in Kolhapur history. A must sightseeing point)

This place took me by surprise,  it is not very big but nice things for especially children to look at, well planned. The small aquarium on the bottom floor is probably one of the coolest things unless you like to check out the dinosaur on the top first 😮...no worries it is not alive...anyhow, fantasy can get ahead of you here so on a rainy day when the kids are bored take a round here and learn something about your history.
Very well presented museum that’s entertaining as well as educational and suitable for all ages. Takes about 3 hours to visit at a leisurely pace.
I don't understand the German, but I enjoy the visit anyway.
It was very clean and nice presentation. We enjoyed visiting the museum.
Great museum with absolutely insane insight at the topics.
Good food and a wide variety to choose from.  I've been here several times and never had something that I didn't like.
Not the best food or coffee in town but its very centric and cheap. I recommend it if you are on a rush, if you want more quality food not the best choice.
Great lunch spot. Food, prices and service always good. Wide selection on buffet and easy place for a group to eat.
Good food. Nice place for big crowds
Food is good the place is clean....    all you can eat buffet is the popular thing hear
Best persian restaurent in the city. Love it!
Very small restaurant but it was clean, service was friendly and prompt, and the food was great.
Food food unlike anything I had ever tasted. Pricy though.

Some of the best Persian grilled food, rice is always perfectly cooked. This couple has been doing what they do for a very long time and they are great at it. Fesenjoon is amazing and their baklava is the best in the city. They are always very kind, and the restaurant has a cozy atmosphere, everything to make you feel welcome!
Top quality. Great taste. Very good owner's. Will always come back 😁

One of the best Italian restaurants in Dublin,  in my opinion, for many years. Recently, the restaurant has been refurbished and is now even cosier and more comfortable than it used to be. Also, the menu is very keenly priced and the early-bird menu is especially good value with the Bellini thrown in at no extra charge. The Italian staff are all totally professional, efficient, friendly and welcoming.

The staff was nice and friendly but the dish I had wasn't that great. The presentation was very good but taste and texture could have been better.

Looking at the other reviews, everyone seems to like so maybe it was just me. I will try something different next time.

For everyone else, go there and make up you own mind.

Visited this restaurant by chance on a quiet weeknight. Service was superb as was the food. Mushroom ravioli was the best we’ve ever had compared to many other similar restaurants (our favourite dish). Reasonable prices for the area with many specials. We will definitely be back!

Excellent food and excellent service, went here for a family get together and went for the set menu. Everyone raved about the starters and main courses. Excellent wine too. Slightly disappointed I didn't get the pizza as it looked amazing going to other tables. I'll definitely be back for the pizza, I might be changing my review to five stars. Keep up the excellent work folks! Viva Italia!

Best Italian restaurant in Dublin. 
Definitely our favourite place to have meals whether it's just a quick lunch or romantic dinner!!!
Highly recommended! 10/10

This is a lovely coffee shop with some healthy and delicious food options. Their coffee are delicious and staff and really pleasant. They also have free WiFi which is a bonus for the on-the-go salesman like myself. Oh. And they have couches too if you feel like relaxing while dining here. Prices are very reasonable too 😊

Loved this little resturant so much! Waitrons are so friendly, food is amazing and coffee is incredible. All cakes and sweet treats are made fresh and look divine!

Definitely will go back!
Very good service with friendly staff.  Bar one and red velvet cake were both delicious.
Good value for money. We like the sunday toast.

Brilliant freshly ground coffee. I havent eaten here. Wonderful environment for 1 on 1 meetings. Complete with several comfy couches for relaxing while reading or working. Free fast wireless internet too.

It’s beautiful and you could see a lot of Freud’s collections in the reading room. If the weather is nice, the garden will open, and it’s quite good to seat there for a little while.
However, since it’s not big it may then be a lit bit crowded if you visit on weekends.
This place gives you a sense of peace. Everything in the right place, harmony and calmness. Spend some time in Freud's garden, especially if it's a sunny day.
I went here when I was studying abroad. It was quaint and full of history. I enjoyed walking around the house, feeling relaxed and seeing first-hand what I have read about for so long!

I absolutely loved this place! It is quite small but you can easily stay there for a couple of hours to see everything. 

You get a good insight into Freud's life in London, how he got here and the work he's done. There is a whole room with the possessions and works of his daughter and a couple of sketches and a painting from Salvador Dali too! 

The beautiful garden garden at the back is lovely in the Spring and the summer. 

The entrance tickets that you buy are valid for a year (the guy told us that at the ticket office, but that could change at any moment so don't hold me to that) and they do take cards! 

I'd highly recommend this place!
Loved this museum. This was a house that Freud actually lived and worked in.  It showed about has life and work. Told how he ended up living there. Worth a visit.

Great food, decent beer, very cool atmosphere. Place is pretty pricey, especially for their beers. They sell 1 liter pints and 2 liter boots, but it's the same price per oz. As their smaller selections, so a boot can easily cost you over $30

Wonderful place to drop in for high quality music, food and drink.  Easy place to drop in and talk to friendly locals if you're alone, and very accommodating if you want to reserve a table to meet, dine and dance with a large group of friends.  The food is always good, the music never disappoints.  So gotta give 'em 5 stars.

We had a wonderful experience at Speisekammer. My husband took me there for my birthday. The food was delicious,  the cocktail I ordered was great and the service was good too. I ordered the lamb shank,  which came with some really tasty charred brussel sprouts. My husband also enjoyed the cabbage rolls he ordered. What a find!

I wish I would have written a detailed review on this place immediately, because I would have been able to describe it better. The food was better than expected, and I went in with good expectations. It took a about 10-15 minutes to get my food, which is a good thing in my opinion--it was definitely freshly cooked. Unfortunately, I was working at the time and couldn't enjoy a beer to go with my meal. The price was good, and they give fair portions. Check this place out! I can't wait to make an excuse to go back to Alameda just to go here again.

So this was a pretty cool and funky place. It was a nice afternoon in Alameda, so we sat outside with our dog. The pretzel and cheese was outstanding, and the currywurst was decent. Drinks were good, but a little slow. Maybe our server was baked

Among the best botanical gardens in the world. Interesting outdoor spaces but also many indoor collections if you are visiting on a rainy day. Wonderful collection of cacti. Beautiful nature paths. Definitely a worthy part of any visit to Berlin.

This was the best botanical garden that i have visited during early Spring. Its very well priced and the glass houses were brilliant, ferns, cactus, Tropical, so many different rooms and each was throughly enjoyed. 
Take a picnic if the weather if good and even a few beers like i saw some locals. 
The coffee shop also serves lovely cold, big beers) Thumbs up on that and the gift shop has some lovely items.

The outside grounds weren't quite in bloom yet but they were still beautiful. The many and massive greenhouses were amazing. Different regions of the world, different climates and all were meticulously cared for.

Beautiful Botanical garden. They have plants from all continents. It is also interesting in winter time because the glasshouses with plants are huge. So you don't have to be afraid that you wont have anything to see if it's winter.

It is my most visited place in Berlin. I had two times a year ticket and I used it many times. I was there in average 2 times a week. 

The vegan soup is awesome! The houses are the perfect friend in winter months. The gardens are great for the summer. 

For all touristic and local interest's important place! 

You can walk by food from breitenbachplatz
A nice square to hang out
A historical church and touristic attraction near the city council.
Are the you came Don Cook. These are you came Thank You! The as a came gave!
Schöne alte Kirche in Kassel.
